reviewText: Good series. Quality good for the price.

I bought this to see the TV Series remake of the classic film with Spencer Tracy.  The DVD itself was total crap.  I tried 3 different DVD players including a region free player and a brand new one.  The dvd skipped, stalled and froze completely making it impossible to watch the episodes.  Not sure what process the manufacturer used but it obviously didn't work.  I even tried to play it on my computer DVD drive and the disk ejected immediately and would not read
Another old show that was very entertaining.
good old tv program good stories

The picture quality is not very good on this item. If you are fussy like I am about the clarity of the video, this DVD will not be enjoyable for you. I tried this one disk and would have ordered others if the quality level was better, but this one was enough to stop me.

Purchased from Amazon.com.  The Northwest Passage t.v. series Volume 3 was filmed in color at the MGM Studios in Hollywood in 1959 and stars Keith Larsen, Buddy Ebsen, and Don Burnett and was  directed by Jacques Tourneur, Alan Grosland, Jr. and George Waggner.  This volume contains exciting adventures of Major Robert Rogers and his Rangers defending America's original 13 British colonies in the frontier during the French and Indian Wars of 1754-1763.  These stories provide wholesome viewing for the entire family.
